javadoc:
Class to represent an application's version information.

The version format is \d\.\d(\.\d)?(\-.+)?

Examples:

  • 7.4
  • 7.4.1
  • 7.4.1-DEV

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment: Creates a new ApplicationVersion object from the given version string.

throws.comment:
if the version string failed to parse.  The 
   exception's message has more detailed information about why it failed.

methods.javadoc:
Gets the major version.
@return The major version.
methods.name: getMajor

methods.javadoc:
Gets the minor version.
@return The minor version.
methods.name: getMinor

methods.javadoc:
Gets the patch version.
@return The patch version.
methods.name: getPatch
